Lighter validation alternatives:

**Zod** (13KB): De facto standard. Great DX, huge ecosystem. Used by tRPC, React Hook Form, shadcn.

**Valibot** (~1KB per schema): Modular, tree-shakeable. Only imports what you use. 90% smaller for simple schemas.

**ArkType** (~5KB): Type-level validation using TS syntax. Fastest runtime performance. Newest.

**Comparison**:
```typescript
// Zod
const UserSchema = z.object({ name: z.string(), age: z.number().min(0) });

// Valibot
const UserSchema = v.object({ name: v.string(), age: v.pipe(v.number(), v.minValue(0)) });

// ArkType
const User = type({ name: "string", "age": "number >= 0" });
```

If bundle size matters (edge workers, mobile web): **Valibot**.
If ecosystem matters (tRPC, React Hook Form integration): **Zod**.
If you want the fastest runtime: **ArkType**.
